PODS 1-4: [STATUS: STABLE] [CONTENTS: UNKNOWN/LOCKED] (Stasis Pods)
----------------------------------------
Four human forms float in clear, coffin-like tanks. Condensation fogs the glass at the edges. Each is connected to a tangle of cables that feed into a central monitoring station—now dark, its screens showing only the Ares logo and the words "PROJECT CHIMERA - TIER 1."
They could be anything. Ages? Hard to tell through the frosted glass and the pale blue fluid. Late teens? Young adults? They wear thin, featureless jumpsuits. No weapons. No visible cyberware. Just... people. Sleeping.
Or maybe not sleeping. Maybe something else.
The scientist you grabbed won't stop staring at them. When asked, he just shakes his head and whispers: "You don't understand what you took."
Static has been running comparisons between the AI core's architecture and the biometric data flickering weakly on the pod monitors. There are matches. Patterns. He won't say what they mean yet.
The pods hum. Low. Constant. Like a heartbeat you can feel in your teeth.
You don't know if they're victims. Weapons. Something worse. All you know is they're yours now—and Ares wants them back.

